    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sport resembling hockey, with two teams of four players each, played on horseback with long-handled mallets and the objective of propelling a wooden or plastic ball down a grass field and through a goal. It is said to be the oldest of equestrian sports.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
